        <p><a href="/locations/dubai/business-bay/">Business Bay</a> has emerged as Dubai's commercial centre, home to thousands of companies ranging from startups to regional headquarters. Corporate translation needs here include employment contracts, commercial agreements, and regulatory filings.</p>
        
        <p><a href="/locations/dubai/difc/">DIFC</a> serves as the financial centre with its own courts and regulatory framework. While DIFC operates in English, companies here regularly need Arabic translations for mainland dealings—banking relationships, property transactions, and employee visa processing.</p>
        
        <p><a href="/locations/dubai/jlt/">JLT and DMCC</a> house thousands of free zone companies. Company formation documents, visa applications, and trade license amendments all commonly require translation between English and Arabic. We understand DMCC's specific documentation requirements.</p>
        
        <h3>Industrial and Emerging Areas</h3>
        <p>Dubai South, near Al Maktoum Airport, is growing as a logistics and aviation hub. Companies establishing here need translation for licensing, customs documentation, and staff visas. We serve this developing area with the same responsiveness as established districts.</p>
        
        <p>Jebel Ali Free Zone (JAFZA), one of the world's largest free zones, requires extensive documentation for company operations. Import-export businesses need translation for customs purposes, contracts with international suppliers, and regulatory compliance.</p>
        
        <p>Dubai Silicon Oasis and other technology-focused areas attract businesses with complex documentation needs—intellectual property filings, technology licensing agreements, and investor documents. We handle the technical terminology these sectors require.</p>
